# SEO & PWA

## Server-side meta (primary)

Public SEO is rendered on the server via React Router v7 `meta` exports per route.

| Route type | Where to configure |
|------------|-------------------|
| Static list pages | `STATIC_ROUTE_META` in `src/lib/seo/meta.ts` or `staticPageMeta()` in route wrapper |
| Dynamic detail pages | `loader` + `meta` in route wrapper; helpers in `src/lib/seo/loaders.ts` |
| Global JSON-LD | `src/root.tsx` |
| robots.txt | `src/routes/robots[.]txt.ts` |
| sitemap.xml | `src/routes/sitemap[.]xml.ts` |

Example detail route wrapper:

```tsx
import { heroDetailLoader, heroDetailMeta } from "@/lib/seo/loaders"

export const loader = heroDetailLoader
export const meta = heroDetailMeta
export { HeroDetailPage as default } from "@/pages/HeroDetailPage"
```

## Admin SEO settings vs SSR

Admin panel SEO (`/admin/seo`) stores overrides in **localStorage** via `useSiteSettings()`. These apply client-side only — crawlers and social share previews use SSR meta from route loaders.

To change production meta for static routes, update `STATIC_ROUTE_META` or the route's `meta` export.

## Analytics

Set `VITE_GA_ID` (GA4 measurement ID) in `.env` / Vercel env vars. Loaded in `src/root.tsx` when present.

## PWA manifest

Configured in `vite.config.ts` via `vite-plugin-pwa`:

- `theme_color` and `background_color`: `#0D0E12` (matches `brand-bg`)
- Icons: `public/icons/pwa-192x192.png`, `pwa-512x512.png`, `apple-touch-icon.png`
- `lang`: `vi`, `start_url`: `/`

Do not change theme colors to raw hex outside design tokens when updating manifest.

## Site config

Global site name/description: `src/config/site.ts`. Admin SEO settings persisted via `useSiteSettings()` (client overlay).

## Verification

```bash
npm run test:e2e -- e2e/seo-ssr.spec.ts
./scripts/smoke-ssr.sh https://YOUR_DOMAIN
```
